      "Herman Miller Aeron chair, Size B (medium), in Graphite. This is the remastered version with PostureFit SL.\n\n1. 8Z Pellicle mesh — breathable and incredibly comfortable\n2. Fully adjustable arms, tilt limiter, and seat angle\n3. PostureFit SL supports both sacrum and lumbar\n4. Size B fits most people 5'2\" to 6'0\"\n5. Manufactured in 2021 — Herman Miller warranty may still transfer\n\nI sat in this chair for 8+ hours a day for two years and my back has never felt better. Upgrading to the Embody. This chair retails for $1,400+.",
      "King size platform bed frame in solid acacia wood with a natural finish. Clean, modern lines with a slatted headboard.\n\nThis frame doesn't need a box spring — the slat system is built in and provides great support. Headboard is 45 inches tall. Ground clearance is about 12 inches, so plenty of room for under-bed storage. Holds a standard king mattress (76x80). Very sturdy — no creaking. Disassembles with a hex key for transport.",
      "La-Z-Boy Greyson leather recliner in dark brown. The kind of chair you sink into and don't want to get up from.\n\n• Genuine top-grain leather — not bonded\n• Power reclining with USB charging port\n• Padded chaise for full leg support\n• Lumbar support built into the backrest\n• Measures 40\"W x 40\"D x 42\"H\n\nBought this two years ago for $1,200. The leather has aged beautifully — no cracks, peeling, or wear spots. Smoke-free, pet-free home.",
