      "Weber Spirit II E-310 gas grill with 3 burners and 529 sq inches of cooking space. This grill has been a workhorse for two summers.\n\n1. 30,000 BTU main burners\n2. Porcelain-enameled cast-iron cooking grates\n3. Built-in lid thermometer\n4. Grease management system makes cleanup easy\n5. Folding side tables and tool hooks\n6. Propane tank NOT included\n\nGrates and flavorizer bars are in good shape. Just cleaned everything thoroughly. Igniter works perfectly every time. Selling because I upgraded to a pellet smoker.",
      "Complete 6-piece patio conversation set. Includes a loveseat, 2 armchairs, a coffee table, and 2 ottomans. Wicker with tan cushions.\n\n• Steel frame with hand-woven PE rattan — weather resistant\n• Cushions are 4-inch thick with removable, washable covers\n• Coffee table has tempered glass top\n• Ottomans double as extra seating\n• Set up takes about 30 minutes — all hardware included\n\nUsed on a covered porch for one season. Cushions have been stored inside during winter. No fading, no tears. This was $800 new.",
      "Brand new cedar raised garden bed kit — never assembled. Bought two and only needed one.\n\nDimensions are 4 feet x 8 feet x 11 inches tall. Western red cedar is naturally rot-resistant so no chemical treatment needed. All hardware and corner brackets are included. Assembly takes about 20 minutes with just a screwdriver. Perfect for vegetables, herbs, or flowers. Cedar smells amazing and looks beautiful in any yard.",
      "EGO Power+ 21-inch self-propelled lawn mower. The 56V battery-powered mower that actually rivals gas performance.\n\n• 56V 7.5Ah ARC Lithium battery included\n• Self-propelled with variable speed\n• 3-in-1: mulch, bag, or side discharge\n• LED headlights for early morning or evening mowing\n• Folds flat for compact storage\n• Weather-resistant construction\n\nUsed for one season on a quarter-acre lot. Battery still holds a full charge and mows the whole yard. Charger included. Selling because we moved to a condo.",
