      "48-foot outdoor string lights with shatterproof LED bulbs. These are the Edison-style warm white bulbs that give your patio that perfect ambiance.\n\n1. 15 sockets spaced 3 feet apart\n2. LED bulbs last 15,000+ hours\n3. Shatterproof — won't break if they swing in the wind\n4. Weatherproof — rated for permanent outdoor use\n5. End-to-end connectable — link up to 8 strands\n\nBrand new in the box. Bought extras for a party and never opened this set. Retails for $55.",
      "Complete 12-piece garden tool set with a carrying tote. Everything you need to get started in the garden.\n\nIncludes: trowel, transplanter, cultivator, weeder, pruning shears, garden fork, kneeling pad, spray bottle, plant ties, gloves, dibber, and a heavy-duty canvas carrying bag. The hand tools have aluminum heads with ergonomic rubber grips. Pruning shears are stainless steel with a safety lock. Great starter set or gift for someone getting into gardening. Brand new — never used.",
      "Simpson MegaShot 3100 PSI gas pressure washer. This thing cleans driveways, siding, decks, and fences like nobody's business.\n\n• Honda GCV170 engine — reliable and easy to start\n• 3100 PSI at 2.4 GPM\n• Comes with 5 quick-connect nozzle tips\n• 25-foot high-pressure hose\n• Onboard detergent tank\n\nUsed it maybe 10 times over two years. Runs perfectly — starts on the first or second pull every time. Oil changed before storage. Just don't need it anymore since we moved to a place with an HOA that handles exterior cleaning.",
      "Hammock with a steel stand — set it up anywhere, no trees required. Perfect for the backyard, patio, or even indoors.\n\nThe hammock is cotton rope with hardwood spreader bars. Stand is powder-coated steel that breaks down into pieces for storage. Total length is about 15 feet. Weight capacity is 450 lbs. Comes with a carrying bag. I've spent many lazy Sunday afternoons in this thing. Selling because we're downsizing our patio setup. Very comfortable and easy to assemble.",
