      "Set of 2 Adirondack chairs in classic white. HDPE recycled plastic — looks like painted wood but requires zero maintenance.\n\n• Won't splinter, crack, peel, or rot\n• UV stabilized — color won't fade\n• Contoured seat and wide armrests\n• Folds flat for winter storage\n• 300 lb weight capacity each\n• Stainless steel hardware throughout\n\nThese are the nice ones, not the cheap plastic chairs from the hardware store. Used for one season. Just wipe them down and they look brand new. Selling as a pair only.",
      "Concrete pedestal bird bath with a classic fluted column design. Stands about 28 inches tall with a 20-inch diameter bowl.\n\nThis is real cast concrete — heavy and substantial. It's developed a lovely aged patina that looks beautiful in a garden setting. The bowl has a gentle slope so birds of all sizes can use it safely. Base and bowl separate into two pieces for easier transport but you'll want two people — it's about 65 lbs total. Perfect focal point for a garden bed or patio corner.",
