      "Complete snowboard setup: Burton Custom 156cm board, Burton Cartel bindings (Medium), and Burton Ruler boots (size 10).\n\n• Burton Custom is the best all-mountain board ever made\n• Cartel bindings — responsive with comfortable ankle straps\n• Ruler boots have the speed zone lacing — takes 10 seconds\n• Board has minor base scratches — normal from riding\n• Edges are sharp and recently waxed\n• Boots are in great shape — no pack-out issues\n\nThis setup does everything — groomers, trees, park, powder. Selling because I switched to a split board for backcountry. Would cost $900+ to buy this setup new.",
      "Wilson Pro Staff RF97 Autograph tennis racket. This is the Roger Federer signature model — the racket that serious players love.\n\nHead size is 97 sq inches, weight is 340g strung, balance is 31cm. Currently strung with Luxilon ALU Power at 50 lbs — still has plenty of life. This racket rewards clean ball-striking with incredible feel and control. Not for beginners — it's a player's racket. Cosmetically in good shape with some paint wear on the bumper guard (normal). Comes with a Wilson racket cover.",
